Two men aged 33 and 38 are expected to appear in the
Bloemfontein Magistrates Court on Monday, 27 June. They are facing charges of attempted murder, defeating the
ends of justice, reckless and negligent driving. This is after a shooting incident that occurred near
Pellesier in Bloemfontein. On Friday 24 June Parkweg police received a lookout about a
heavily armed suspect who just robbed a liquor store in Aliwal North. Cops’ spokesperson Sergeant Sinah Mpakane said an activation
plan was immediately executed and two cars, fitting the same description
circulated, were spotted near the Casino. “Police attempted to stop both cars, a White Mercedes Benz
and Maroon Toyota Hi-Lux. Both cars failed to stop, and a chase ensued with the
suspects firing shots toward the police. Police retaliated,” Mpakane said in a
statement. Police managed to intercept the Toyota Hilux and two
suspects were arrested on the scene while the third one managed to escape.
Inside the car, cops managed to recover two 9mm firearms, two rifles, an R5
Cartridge along with four magazines and live rounds of ammunition. The second car, a Mercedes-Benz was spotted at Bayswater
after a long chase and one cartridge was found inside the car with a bullet
hole in it. Police are still on the lookout for the third suspect. Mpakane urged anyone with information that can lead to the
arrest of the third suspect or who can provide police with information related
to this incident is requested to call Captain Khoali of Parkweg Detectives on
082 526 2713.